tweet: He told me Wall Street expected him to "give away the store." Instead, he was a superb steward of the city's finances, initiated the hiring of NYC police officers to pre-fiscal crisis levels. His vision for NYC? A gorgeous mosaic. RIP Mayor Dinkins. 2/2

Mayor David N. Dinkins was a great mayor for NYC. I know. I was there. I was City Hall Bureau Chief for NY Newsday during his administration. He taught me about systemic racism in private conversations and in Blue Room press conferences. 1/2

I am looking to make space for the next chapter after I leave @knightfnd on Feb. 2. I will participate in Knight Media Forum March 2-4. I hope you will too. Again, thanks to all the people in the field doing the work. Support them. Fund them. Start with @NewsMatch now. 4/4 TKS

This has been a tough year for all of us. Like so many people, the pandemic led me to consider making major changes in my life. Until March, my husband, an editor at @nytimes, and I have lived in different cities. We don't want to do that in 2021. 3/4

Am also deeply grateful to @ibarguen for giving me this opportunity in 2014 & inspiring local journ strategy. Am also so grateful to the rockstar KF Journalism team: @LaSharah @kbmiami @pcheung630 @jonbelgrad & @nickswyter now at NYT.  2/4
